<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A1406035004">
<title>
Piston
</title>
<topic id = "AENAP70A1406035005">
<title>
Visual inspection
</title>
<ptxt>
Inspect piston for faults, cracks or other damages.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Damaged or faulty piston should be replaced.
</ptxt>
</topic>
<topic id = "AENAP70A1406035006">
<title>
Piston diameter
</title>
<ptxt>
As indicated in figure, piston diameter should be measured at specified position “a” 10.0 mm (0.3937 in.) from piston skirt end in the direction perpendicular to piston pin.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Piston diameter specification
</title>
<ptxt>
Standard size (used piston): 72.975 – 72.990 mm (2.8730 – 2.8736 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Standard size (new piston with coating): 72.977 – 73.010 mm (2.8732 – 2.8744 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9T401142038.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "31.996mm" ver = "01" gw = "218" gh = "74"/>
